In the field of [[bioengineering]], '''biofunctionalisation''' (or biofunctionalization) is the modification of a material to have  [[function (biology)|biological function]] and/or [[biological target|stimulus]], whether permanent or temporary while at the same time being [[biocompatible material|biologically compatible]].<ref name="isbn3-642-21948-9">{{cite book |vauthors=Gübitz G, Nyanhongo GS, Walter S | title = Biofunctionalization of Polymers and their Applications (Advances in Biochemical Engineering Biotechnology) | publisher = Springer | location = Berlin | year = 2011 | pages = | isbn = 3-642-21948-9 | oclc = | doi =  }}</ref><ref name="isbn3-527-31381-8">{{cite book | author = Kumar CSSR | title = Biofunctionalization of Nanomaterials (Nanotechnologies for the Life Sciences) | publisher = John Wiley & Sons | location = Chichester | year = 2006 | pages = | isbn = 3-527-31381-8 | url= http://www.wiley.com/WileyCDA/WileyTitle/productCd-3527313818.html }}</ref><ref name=Das_2012>{{cite journal |vauthors=Das M, Bandyopadhyay D, Singh RP, Harde H, Kumar S, Jain S | title = Orthogonal biofunctionalization of magnetic nanoparticles via "clickable" poly(ethylene glycol) silanes: a "universal ligand" strategy to design stealth and target-specific nanocarriers | journal = Journal of Materials Chemistry |date=January 2012 | volume = 22 | issue = 47 | pages = 24652 | doi = 10.1039/C2JM34571D }}</ref>

Various types of [[implant (medicine)|medical implants]] are designed to biofunctionalize so that they can replace or repair a defective biological function and are accepted by the host organism.<ref name="pmid18831592">{{cite journal |vauthors=de Mel A, Jell G, Stevens MM, Seifalian AM | title = Biofunctionalization of biomaterials for accelerated in situ endothelialization: a review | journal = Biomacromolecules | volume = 9 | issue = 11 | pages = 2969–79 |date=November 2008 | pmid = 18831592 | doi = 10.1021/bm800681k }}</ref><ref name="pmid22324003">{{cite journal | author = Hanawa T | title = A comprehensive review of techniques for biofunctionalization of titanium | journal = J Periodontal Implant Sci | volume = 41 | issue = 6 | pages = 263–72 |date=December 2011 | pmid = 22324003 | pmc = 3259234 | doi = 10.5051/jpis.2011.41.6.263 }}</ref>

